/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 72.0 563.0 Tm (In a structured LLM evaluation pipeline, we observed verdict variance that initially) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 549.0 Tm (looked like model nondeterminism and turned out to be driven by non-evidence fields in) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 535.0 Tm (the gate input. A single non-evidence field, a wall-clock fetch timestamp, was) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 521.0 Tm (sufficient to induce verdict variance across runs. Removing it restored full determinism) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 507.0 Tm (on byte-identical input for the tested case.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72.0 487.0 Tm (Attempting to generalize the cleanup to other fields classified as metadata caused) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 473.0 Tm (verdict drift on boundary cases, forcing reverts. The useful finding is not a list of) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 459.0 Tm (safe fields but a discipline: field classification cannot be done by inspection alone) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 445.0 Tm (and requires per-field empirical verification.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72.0 425.0 Tm (This suggests that some apparent nondeterminism in structured evaluation systems may be) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 411.0 Tm (an artifact of unstable input construction rather than model behavior alone.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72.0 391.0 Tm (This is a methodology note from small-scale diagnostic work. It is not broad validation.) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 377.0 Tm (It is shared because the pattern is useful for teams building similar evaluation) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 363.0 Tm (pipelines.) Tj
