1 0 0 1 72.0 720.0 Tm (The narrow finding is solid within this diagnostic setting: a wall-clock timestamp in) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 706.0 Tm (gate-visible input caused verdict variance that was not model nondeterminism. Removing) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 692.0 Tm (it improved input determinism.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72.0 672.0 Tm (The broader generalization, that non-evidence fields can be systematically identified) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 658.0 Tm (and removed by inspection, is not supported by our testing. Field classification by) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 644.0 Tm (inspection failed at least twice on fields that looked reasonable to remove. The) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 630.0 Tm (discipline that holds up is empirical verification per field, not global cleanup.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72.0 610.0 Tm (After the initial finding, we applied the same methodology to two additional evaluation) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 596.0 Tm (pipelines in our own work. One showed no observable drift after cleanup. The other) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 582.0 Tm (showed verdict drift on a canonical test case. The mixed result reinforces the canary) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 568.0 Tm (discipline: drift is pipeline-specific, and the methodology catches drift that) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 554.0 Tm (inspection misses.) Tj
1 0 0 1 72.0 534.0 Tm (Small residual variance may remain even after removing identified variance sources. We) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 520.0 Tm (did not fully characterize whether that residual variance came from API-level behavior) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 506.0 Tm (at temperature 0 or from additional input fields we had not identified. That question) Tj
1 0 0 1 84.0 492.0 Tm (remains open.) Tj
